Programming is how you get computers to solve problems
there has to be a programmer, who will tell the computer want to do, or how to solve the problems
logic of programming -sequence (running structions in order), -selection(making choices), -repetition(doing the same thing more than once)
A computer program is a sequence of instructions written using a Computer Programming Language to perform a specified task by the computer, also called a computer software
Computer program instructions are also called program source code and computer programming is also called program coding.

****** English Language, which is a well-known Human Interface Language

The basic elements of programming languages: Programming Environment, Basic Syntax, Data Types, Variables, Keywords, Basic Operators, Decision Making, Loops, Numbers, Characters, Arrays, Strings, Functions, File I/O